---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="JobAgent — Automated Job Search Pipeline" description="A fully automated job search and application pipeline — discovers, scores, tailors, and tracks applications end to end.">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pt-32 pb-24">

    <a href="/projects" class="text-sm text-slate-500 hover:text-white transition-colors mb-8 inline-block">← All projects</a>

    <div class="mb-2">
      <span class="text-xs font-medium text-green-400 bg-green-950/50 rounded px-2.5 py-1">Live · 8,000+ jobs</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mt-4 mb-2">JobAgent</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-slate-400 mb-10">Automated job search & application pipeline.</p>

    <div class="space-y-8">

      <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-green-500 bg-slate-900/60 p-6">
        <p class="text-slate-300 text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium">
          "If you're going to do something tedious and repetitive hundreds of times, automate it."
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">The problem</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          Job searching at scale is a nightmare. Hundreds of job boards, ATS systems, and portals — each requiring manual CV tailoring, custom cover letters, and application tracking. I needed a system, not a process.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">What it does</h2>
        <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
          {[
            { step: "01", title: "Discovery", body: "Scrapes LinkedIn, Indeed, Greenhouse, Recruitee, and Workday ATS across 50+ companies" },
            { step: "02", title: "Scoring", body: "GPT-4o-mini scores each job against my profile (0–10). Filters out noise automatically" },
            { step: "03", title: "Tailoring", body: "Generates a tailored CV and cover letter for every score ≥8 job, based on the actual job description" },
            { step: "04", title: "Tracking", body: "Excel tracker + session summaries. Full pipeline state visible at all times" },
          ].map(item => (
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/40 p-5">
              <div class="text-blue-400 text-xs font-bold mb-2">{item.step}</div>
              <div class="text-white font-medium mb-1">{item.title}</div>
              <div class="text-slate-400 text-sm">{item.body}</div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">Numbers</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          {[
            { value: "8,000+", label: "Jobs discovered" },
            { value: "300+", label: "Applications tailored" },
            { value: "50+", label: "Companies tracked" },
          ].map(stat => (
            <div class="text-center rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/40 p-4">
              <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">{stat.value}</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">{stat.label}</div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-white font-semibold text-xl mb-3">Stack</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          Python end to end. JobSpy for LinkedIn/Indeed scraping, direct API integration with Greenhouse/Recruitee/Workday. OpenAI gpt-4o-mini for scoring and tailoring. Local SQLite database. Power Automate chains for pipeline orchestration.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 pt-8 border-t border-slate-800 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      {["Automation", "Python", "OpenAI", "Web Scraping", "SQLite", "Power Automate"].map(tag => (
        <span class="text-xs text-blue-400 bg-blue-950/40 rounded px-2 py-0.5">{tag}</span>
      ))}
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>
